  "title": "connectNumericMenu not working with same `start` value in `items`",
  "body": "<!--\r\n  Thanks for participating in this project! We will try to answer as soon as possible 🙏\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug 🐛**\r\n\r\nconnectNumericMenu is not working when there are more than one items with same `start` value in `items`.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce 🔍**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. Open `numeric-menu.stories.js`\r\n2. Add the following story:\r\n```js\r\n  .add(\r\n    'same start value',\r\n    withHits(({ search, container, instantsearch }) => {\r\n      search.addWidget(\r\n        instantsearch.widgets.numericMenu({\r\n          container,\r\n          attribute: 'price',\r\n          items: [\r\n            { label: 'All' },\r\n            { start: 1, end: 2, label: '1-2' },\r\n            { start: 1, end: 10, label: '1-10' },\r\n          ],\r\n        })\r\n      );\r\n    })\r\n  )\r\n```\r\n\r\n3. Click `1-2`.\r\n4. `1-10` is selected instead.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior 💭**\r\n`1-2` is supposed to be selected\r\n\r\n**Screenshots 🖥**\r\n\r\n![Kapture 2019-09-17 at 14 14 45](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/499898/65040805-88ad0a00-d955-11e9-9c10-31658b4e55c9.gif)",
